transcription.text:
Speaker 1: Thank you for calling customer service. I can help you.

Speaker 2: Yes, can you bring up a prescription number or my name, whichever is easiest?

Speaker 1: Sure, what's your name and birthday?

Speaker 2: James Mark Graph, M-A-R-K V-R-A-F as in Frank.

Speaker 1: Two 18 53, 1953?

Speaker 2: Okay, I can help you.

Speaker 1: So I, I thought we had ordered some 10 milligram—

Speaker 2: Uh, Viagra?

Speaker 1: What is it? VG, VR, VG, whatever the three letters are.

Speaker 2: You say?

Speaker 1: Yes.

Speaker 2: And what came in was 50, and it looks like just generic. I don't know if it's that new because the advertising was—

Speaker 1: You know, take it in 11 minutes, blah blah blah, and the prescription says wait an hour.

Speaker 2: Okay, so—

Speaker 1: Okay, so all the same thing.

Speaker 2: Sure, go ahead. So all, all Viagras fall under the Sydney Phil—

Speaker 1: Umbrella, so any, any Viagra is going to say up to an hour.

Speaker 2: But most men report that it happens anywhere between 11 to 24 minutes.

Speaker 1: Um, you didn't get the wrong one if you were trying to get the AGV, and I can submit that and have that shipped to—

Speaker 2: You, uh, we don't carry 10 milligrams. So it's 25 milligrams, 50s, or 100. That's fine.

Speaker 1: But I definitely wanted the AGV instead of the old one. Are you still on Traymont Avenue?

Speaker 2: Yes, I am.

Speaker 1: Okay.

Speaker 2: And this will go out today?

Speaker 1: Be great, and there's 20 pills, right?

Speaker 2: Yes, sir.

Speaker 1: Thank you, I appreciate your help.

Speaker 2: Absolutely, and there's no additional charge, right? Do you want those other ones back?

Speaker 1: We do not, you can try them.

Speaker 2: Okay.

Speaker 1: Wow, okay. Yeah, I definitely wanted the new one. So I do appreciate your help. Thank you. Have a wonderful day.

Speaker 2: Bye.

Speaker 1: Bye, you too.
